<br>
Remarkably free of those annoying posts from people who <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> assume</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that we became druids or wizards because we had a career plan of being taxis for everyone, and should therefore just &quot;quit whining&quot; and port them.<br>
<br>
Yes, I port all the time...my friends, my guildmates, people I've grouped with and remember favorably, and the odd person who I port either cause a) I'm in the mood or b) I'm in dire need of pocket change and they just offered a nice wad of it.  I almost never port commercially anymore...its too much of a headache.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I agree with Wolfypaw...it GETS OLD.  I did <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> become a druid in order to paint myself in yellow, white and black checks and stick an illuminated sign on my head.  I am not shouting &quot;Get yer free buffs here!&quot; through a megaphone.  No where do I recall seeing a message saying I was obligated to heal, str, chloro, DS, and sow anyone who asked, and to be extra quick about it if they spoke dewd-speak to me (&quot;U buff me plz!&quot;)<br>
<br>
And yet there are zones in this game where I have to either grit my teeth and ignore the beggar-spam, or go /role to try and avoid most of it.  I used to try and politely decline all the requests...but that, too GETS OLD, especially since it all too frequently leads to the beggar either arguing back, making incresing silly offers for my help, or becoming downright insulting.<br>
<br>
Heck, I've more then once gone afk in some reasonably safe location without having bothered to set my AFK flag, and come back to a screen of text along these lines:<br>
<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Hail<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Hail<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Hail, Magpye<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Can u sow me?<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Sow plz<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Can u buff?<br>
SomeDude tells you: Can I get sow and ds plz?<br>
SomeDude tells you: Hello?<br>
&lt;SomeDude&gt; Hail, Magpye<br>
SomeDude tells you: I need some buffs<br>
SomeDude tells you: $%#@ $#@$#@ u so RUDE!!!<br>
<br>
Its amazing the conversations people are apparently having in their heads with me, as my character sits there, unminded, and twitching slightly as the engine makes it fidget. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Another thing that always makes me laugh...there's been a few times where I've been hunting on one of my twinks, and heard some person make higher and higher offers for ports.  Clearly they are desperate for a port and no one is porting at the moment.  So if Mags is nearby I'll switch and load her up, do an &quot;/ooc porting from ____&quot; to get their attention, and port them...and its surprising how many of them don't offer to pay anything close to what they were shouting a few minutes before, because they assume I didn't hear their own /ooc's since I wasn't visibily in zone then.  Was one guy in GD late one night who was offering 200pp when I switched and then only paid 20pp for the port.  I don't mind, I'm as likely to port for free as to charge (unless I'm financially low and need every pp I can get), but...it amuses me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
A similar incident: There was one night I was sitting at the Seb orb as my rogue.  Magpye was parked there to port me out after hunting Seb, but I'd had a couple of bad groups and was now sitting outside trying to decide what to do with the evening.  Lots of people standing around /oocing for ports, and several offering quite large sums...100 pp, 250 pp, a diamond (still worth 500 pp or more at the time), a black sapphire, etc. etc. etc...very nice cash it sounded like.  Decided what the heck, I could use some money, I camp Snoww, load Magpye...&quot;Porting from Orb to anywhere, 100 pp per ride&quot;.<br>
<br>
Immeadiately get a FLOOD of angry /ooc and /shout about how high my price is...clearly the old &quot;since they didn't see me before, they assume I don't know what they were offering&quot; act.  100pp was the *least* amount I'd seen anyone offer for a ride out in the last half hour or more.  A cleric who'd been desperately offering a diamond to get a ride to anywhere very happily shelled out 100pp for an express service ride to her destination of choice, and I left the rest to resume their silly /oocing for ports.  If you're not willing to pay a high price, then don't artificially drive up the market...and especially, don't complain when someone offers to port you for less then the ridiculous amount you'd been offering just minutes before.<br>
<br>
 <p><b>Iztariani Moonglow</b> <<a href=http://toddvw.brinkster.net/ageless/>Ageless Wanderers</a>>, Erudite Paladin - <i>Life is good, and then you have to retrieve your corpse</i><br>
"I can't think of anything good to say about the undead...except that it's good they're dead, and soon they'll be the dissassembled undead."
