ask me for plat up front. <p><b><font color="#FF0000",font size="+3">Ruuka Eno</font></b><br><i>Revenant of Innoruuk</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ucassitera.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cassitera</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#778899>(12/2/01 1:29:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: opposite buff beggers</span><hr size=1> There's also a difference between donations and required payment.  For example, we all see those Salvation Army peeps standing outside Nordstrom's or similar department stores ringing their bells during the Christmas shopping season.  When you leave Nordstrom's and pass them by, you're not required to pay them, and they shouldn't be mad if you drop a few coins into their bucket, as opposed to $20.  <br>
<br>
Now, if you're on the bus, more than likely required to shell out $1.25 or so for the transportation, and people don't sit there and try to talk the bus driver out of having to pay or lowering the price or what not (I'm sure there's a few crazy people out there in the world who would try).  It's just expected and required that you pay for that transportation.  If it's a required payment, don't complain about it, especially if the porter tells you up front how much it will cost.  <br>
<br>
Like Mag, I don't accept donations unless I'm hurting for the money.  I have been stiffed a few times, and I've also been paid handsomely a couple times, but this is the life of one who has the ability to get someone from WL to Toxx in however long it takes you to zone.  <br>
<br>
So, note to all &quot;commercial porters&quot;: take a look at your hotkey.  Does it say porting for donations or porting for plat?  If it says donations, do you really mean that, or is that trying to be a sugar-coatted word for plat?  If that's so, change your message because false advertisement sucks.  <br>
<br>
